column45: Calm; ferry just departed before we took the sample; algae growing on the ramp; sunny and hot; light breeze. Rained yesterday in Lana'i City, but we're not sure the rain made it to the coast.
Sunny, 3' shorebreak, water looked clean; light breeze. Rained yesterday in Lana'i City, but we're not sure the rain made it to the coast.

Light breeze, sunny, tide going out, calm water. Did reading 2x: Salinity = 36.2, DO = 6.10 mg/L & 92.1%. People in samll boat docked next to us as we sampled. They arrived just before smapling ~5 min.
Clear water, partly cloudy, 3' shorebreak. 2nd read: Salinity = 36.3, Temp = 26.6, DO = 6.60 mg/L & 99.7%

Receding tide, sunny, no waves, calm water. 4th tubidity  3.97 NTU. *Pre-sampling blank value taken from yesterday's post-sampling blank. Pre-sampling blank step was accidentally skipped before sample was poured into glass vial. Turbidity spare blank read 0.15 NTU and not used.
Receding tide, shorebreak ~ 3ft & small, sunny, light breeze
Calm; some overcast; no wind; no people; water murky brown; 4th turbidity taken 4.76
Calm; clear day; slight swell; 4th turbidity taken 1.31
calm water, looks lightly brown, sunny, no breeze
sunny, light breeze, small swell & shorebreak at collection, water sparkling clear
sunny, partly cloudy(nimbus) high tide at collection, brownish water, 4th TURB 2.89
sunny, partly cloudy(nimbus) high tide at collection, brownish water
sunny, light wind, receding tide, light brown water, 4th Turb 2.76, 5th Turb 2.36
sunny, light wind, receding tide, clear water, shorebreak, 4th Turb 0.93
light wind, clear sky, calm, high tide at 9:23am, harbor water looks brown, lots of rain last week > 1", some rain last night swell last week as well, took 4th turbidity = 5.73
calm water, normal shorebreak, pond full across parking lot from last week's rain, workers pumping water out
